<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1255: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-08T14:00:00-05:00">October 8, 1935—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>58. Department’s confidential instruction, No. 337, September 25. The
                            Department desires you to make no further statement which might appear
                            to commit this Government to any action in accordance with any of the
                            provisions of the Central American General Treaty of Peace and Amity of
                                1923,<note n="42" xml:id="d647fn42">Signed February 7, 1923, <hi rend="italic">Conference on Central American Affairs</hi>, p.
                                287.</note> or which might be intended to imply the possibility of
                            any such action.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>